BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Copom Meeting, Mid-month Inflation, Oil Seminar

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-04-20T03:03:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/brazil-daybook-copom-meeting-mid-month-inflation-oil-seminar.html
The central bank announces  Brazil ’s
benchmark interest rate today after the markets close. The so-
called Selic rate will rise 50 basis-points, or 0.5 percentage
point, to 12.25 percent, according to the median estimate in a
Bloomberg survey of 58 economists.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Brazil’s Trade Minister Fernando Pimentel speaks on radio
program Bom Dia, Ministro at 8 a.m.
*Executives of international oil companies speak at a seminar in
Rio de Janeiro.
*Localiza to host investor day in  New York , with Chief Executive
Officer Salim Mattar and Chief Financial Officer Roberto Mendes
at 8:30 a.m. New York time.  ECONOMY:
*IBGE consumer price index IPCA-15 at 9 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*CPFL (CPFE3 BZ) agreed to merge renewable energy assets with
ERSA
*Cia. Energetica de  Minas Gerais  (CMIG4 BZ) said its Taesa unit
may sell new or existing shares
*HRT (HRTP3 BZ) to issue up to 2.6 billion reais of new stock
for UNX deal
*Aliansce (ALSC3 BZ) posted sales of 1 billion reais in first
quarter
*Vale SA (VALE5 BZ) named Brazil’s Deputy Finance Minister
Nelson Barbosa as a member of its board
*General Shopping Brasil SA (GSHP3 BZ) sold an additional $50
million of perpetual bonds  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 1.1 percent to 66,158.09.
*The real rose 0.9 percent to 1.5763 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
